From a898b780387e5fc01eb53b8ec961a03133b7dbeb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilies CHERGUI <ichergui@nvidia.com>
Date: Thu, 29 Jan 2026 12:18:42 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] Avoid compile errors from math function like macros

Some libc implementation implement certain functions as macros.

This might break our build because the definition of the function
might clash with the macro and also we cannot qualify a macro,
so ::isgreater will fail if isgreater is a macro.

To work around this we need to temporarily push / pop the macros
and define the fallbacks accordingly.

This is fine because the functions themself can only be called
through `cuda::std::isgreater` which avoids the macro issue

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [OE-specific]
Signed-off-by: Michael Schellenberger Costa <miscco@nvidia.com>
Signed-off-by: Ilies CHERGUI <ichergui@nvidia.com>
---
